fulltitle: Secrets of the Temple: How the Federal Reserve Runs the Country
title: Secrets of the Temple: How the Federal Reserve Runs the Country
_filename: _Secrets of the Temple - How the Federal Reserve Runs the Country.mp4
description:
DECEMBER 18, 1987 | William Greider, a correspondent for the Washington Post, spoke to C-SPAN about his book entitled Secrets of the Temple. The book seeks to explore the world of the Federal Reserve. Mr. Greider talked about the history of the Federal Reserve and how its power had grown over the life of the organization. 

For more related content, please visit: https://archive.org/details/@altviewstv-fanclub
